---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Process Automation Chihuahua — Eliminate Manual Work Across Your Operations | Facware"
  description="Every hour your team spends on manual approvals, data entry, and status updates is margin you're leaving on the table. Facware builds workflow automation that eliminates 40%+ of manual operational hours — fixed scope, measurable result."
  canonicalURL="https://facware.com/services/process-automation.html"
  ogDescription="Process automation for mid-market businesses in Chihuahua and the US Southwest. Cut 40%+ of manual ops. Fixed scope, guaranteed outcome. Built by Facware."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "Business Process Automation",
      "description": "We identify, design, and automate the manual workflows costing mid-market businesses in Mexico and the US Southwest 10–30 hours per week in unnecessary labor.",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Facware",
        "url": "https://facware.com"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Chihuahua, Mexico", "US Southwest"],
      "serviceType": "Process Automation",
      "url": "https://facware.com/services/process-automation.html"
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <a href="/#facware_services">Services</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <span aria-current="page">Process Automation</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Process Automation That Eliminates 40%+ of Manual Operational Hours</h1>
      <p>If your team is spending hours on approvals, data entry, status updates, and reconciliation — those hours are your automation backlog. We build the workflows that give that time back, with measurable savings from day one.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">The Real Cost of Manual Work</p>
        <h2 id="problem-heading">Manual processes don't feel expensive — until you add them up</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">At 10–20 hours per week, per team, manual overhead costs $30K–$80K per year in loaded labor. That's before you factor in the errors, delays, and employee frustration.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Approval chains that take days</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Purchase orders sit in inboxes. Invoices wait for a signature. Onboarding tasks are blocked on someone who's out of office. Your process is bottlenecked by people who are doing administrative work instead of high-value work.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Repeated data entry across systems</h3>
          <p class="card-text">The same customer is created in your CRM, your ERP, and your billing system — by hand, by different people, at different times. Errors multiply. Corrections take more time. You end up with three slightly different versions of the same record.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Reporting that consumes a full day</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Every Monday, someone pulls numbers from three places, formats a spreadsheet, and emails it to leadership. This report is already out of date by the time it's read — and it costs 4–6 hours of skilled time every single week.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
  <section class="section section--gray" id="deliverables" aria-labelledby="deliverables-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What We Automate</p>
        <h2 id="deliverables-heading">From approval flows to automated reporting</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">We target the workflows with the highest labor cost and the clearest automation path — not the ones that look impressive on a slide deck.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Approval workflow automation</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Purchase orders, vendor payments, HR requests, expense reports — we design rule-based approval flows that route tasks automatically, escalate on inaction, and maintain a full audit trail. No more inbox bottlenecks.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Data entry & record synchronization</h3>
          <p class="card-text">When a new customer is created in one system, we trigger automatic creation in every downstream system — with data validation and error handling built in. One source of truth, zero manual propagation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Automated reporting & dashboards</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Operational reports that previously took hours to assemble now run on a schedule and land in inboxes automatically. Real-time dashboards surface the metrics your team needs — without someone pulling them manually.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Notification & escalation systems</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Overdue tasks, low inventory, late shipments, expiring contracts — we build the monitoring and alerting layer that tells the right person about the right problem before it becomes a crisis.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="section" id="process" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2 id="process-heading">We find the hours, then we give them back</h2>
      </header>
      <ol class="steps-grid" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Operations Assessment <span class="badge-free">(Free)</span></h3>
            <p>We interview your team leads, map your current workflows, and build a time-cost model of your manual processes. You get a ranked list of automation opportunities with labor savings and ROI estimate for each.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Outcome-Scoped Automation Proposal</h3>
            <p>We propose a fixed-scope engagement targeting the highest-value automation opportunities. You know exactly what we're building, what it will save, and what it will cost — before we start.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Deploy & Measure</h3>
            <p>We build and deploy the automation, train your team on how it works, and track time savings in the first 30 days. You see the ROI before the engagement closes.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF METRICS -->
  <section class="section section--gray" aria-label="Automation results">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="results-content">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">After automation goes live</p>
          <h2>The reports write themselves. Your team works on what matters.</h2>
          <ul class="results-list" role="list">
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>40%+ reduction</strong> in manual operational hours is our benchmark — and it's typically reached in the first month</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Eliminated</strong> weekly manual reporting cycles across multiple client teams</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Same-day approvals</strong> for processes that previously waited 48–72 hours</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>100% outcome-scoped</strong> — we define measurable savings targets before signing anything</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:8px">Get a free operations assessment &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="results-image">
          <img src="/assets/images/facware/resources_facware.png" alt="Process automation results" loading="lazy" width="600" height="450">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED SERVICES -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Related Services</p>
        <h2 id="related-heading">Often paired with process automation</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/erp-integration.html" class="link-primary">ERP & System Integration</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Automation is most powerful when your systems share data automatically. We often combine integration and automation into a single engagement for maximum impact.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/custom-software-development.html" class="link-primary">Custom Software Development</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">When existing platforms can't support the automation logic your process requires, we build the custom layer on top — scoped to your outcome.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/it-consulting.html" class="link-primary">IT Consulting</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Start with a systems audit. We'll map your entire operations stack and identify the highest-ROI automation opportunities before you commit to any build.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BAND -->
  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-band-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-band-heading">Find out what your manual processes are really costing you</h2>
      <p>Use our ROI calculator to estimate your annual manual labor cost — then book 30 minutes with us and we'll show you what can be automated in your first engagement.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a href="/#roi-calculator" class="btn btn-outline-white">Try the ROI calculator</a>
        <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:var(--primary);border-color:#fff">Book your free assessment &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 24px;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
